01:10.660 --> 01:12.720
Last night I dreamt
I could shoot like you.

01:12.730 --> 01:15.090
That's why we're here.

01:15.090 --> 01:16.900
It's a good skill to have.

01:16.900 --> 01:18.900
It's just so heavy.

01:18.900 --> 01:20.100
Sorry.

01:22.100 --> 01:24.070
They're making them lighter now.

01:24.070 --> 01:26.200
I'll get one for you.

01:28.070 --> 01:29.240
Now...

01:31.080 --> 01:33.110
Squeeze the trigger.

01:34.110 --> 01:35.410
Just squeeze it, Charlotte. I am.

01:35.420 --> 01:37.880
You're going to have to squeeze it harder.
But I'm squeezing it.

01:37.890 --> 01:39.950
Ooh! Whoo!

01:41.050 --> 01:42.690
I pulled the trigger at least.

01:42.690 --> 01:44.730
You're aiming for the tins.

01:44.730 --> 01:47.230
You really need to be prepared
for life out here, darling.

01:47.230 --> 01:49.860
I am prepared.
I pulled the trigger.

02:41.950 --> 02:43.280
Oh, Betty.

02:43.280 --> 02:45.750
I hate guns.

02:45.750 --> 02:46.960
A nice sweet tea, ma'am?

02:46.960 --> 02:49.960
Yes, thank you.

03:17.390 --> 03:19.090
Thank you. Betty!

03:19.090 --> 03:21.010
When a lady perspires,
she uses her handkerchief.

03:22.390 --> 03:24.630
Thank you, ma'am.

03:30.970 --> 03:34.270
So, he says, "Why wasn't Jesus
born in New Zealand?"

03:34.270 --> 03:36.040
And the other chap says,

03:36.040 --> 03:38.940
"Because they couldn't find
three wise men and a virgin."

03:38.940 --> 03:39.940
Oh!

03:44.650 --> 03:46.390
So, Charlotte,
how are you settling in?

03:47.390 --> 03:49.120
She's doing superbly.

03:49.120 --> 03:50.390
I know it'll take time.

03:51.390 --> 03:53.360
It's a beautiful island,
but it's just...

03:53.360 --> 03:54.960
Different.

03:54.960 --> 03:57.700
- Oxfordshire, yes?
- But born in London.

03:57.700 --> 03:59.400
Oh, dear, that place
would spoil anyone.

03:59.400 --> 04:02.170
My wife knows how much
this farm means to me.

04:02.170 --> 04:03.740
It's been a long time coming.

04:03.740 --> 04:05.400
And a dream come true.

04:05.410 --> 04:07.970
Well, my husband
can talk me into anything.

04:07.980 --> 04:12.180
You'll get used to it soon enough.
Aye, move on, we did.

04:12.180 --> 04:15.980
When I saw my first weta bug,
I thought it was a cat.

04:15.980 --> 04:19.050
- What's a weta bug?
- -Not to mention the natives.

04:19.050 --> 04:20.720
Who are not as frightening
as they look.

04:20.720 --> 04:22.506
No, but if they look
like the type that could

04:22.518 --> 04:24.160
eat you, then more
than likely, they are.

04:24.390 --> 04:25.390
Oh, George, please.

04:25.960 --> 04:27.960
Well, Charlotte needn't worry.
I mean, look at her.

04:27.960 --> 04:29.930
Not nearly enough meat
on her bones.

04:29.930 --> 04:34.210
- And how far along are you?
- Uh...

04:40.210 --> 04:41.840
Hyah!

04:43.840 --> 04:45.780
Will the grounds be finished
before the baby's born?

04:45.780 --> 04:47.080
That's the plan.

04:47.080 --> 04:50.150
So, it will just be
the three of us.

04:50.150 --> 04:51.150
No more farmhands.

04:58.490 --> 05:02.300
Hello, you beautiful baby.

05:02.300 --> 05:05.500
Could you please just stay in
there for a wee while longer?

05:05.500 --> 05:07.170
All nice and warm.

05:07.170 --> 05:09.300
Until we get the roof on?

05:09.300 --> 05:11.810
And then the house is all yours.

05:11.810 --> 05:13.980
How about that?

05:31.090 --> 05:32.190
Oh. Oh!

05:32.190 --> 05:33.460
Ohh!

05:33.460 --> 05:35.260
Whoo! David!

05:35.260 --> 05:36.770
Oh! Oh, David! Honey?

05:36.770 --> 05:38.430
Coming!

05:38.440 --> 05:40.440
- Charlotte!
- Oh! Oh.

06:39.930 --> 06:41.870
Drop your gun!

06:41.870 --> 06:43.530
Back over there! David, don't!

06:43.540 --> 06:46.400
Darling, just stay calm.

06:46.410 --> 06:47.540
Arthur...

06:47.540 --> 06:50.040
Please, move over there.

06:50.040 --> 06:52.510
P-Please, don't hurt my son.

06:52.510 --> 06:55.120
Back over there.

06:56.120 --> 06:58.150
Arthur, darling.

06:58.150 --> 06:59.150
Now, the safe.

06:59.390 --> 07:00.920
We don't have a safe.

07:00.920 --> 07:03.190
- All right, just please...

07:03.190 --> 07:04.430
please.

07:06.430 --> 07:07.590
Why are you doing this?
David.

07:09.400 --> 07:10.560
After I helped you.

07:10.560 --> 07:12.200
Everything in it.

07:14.400 --> 07:16.940
I gave you work
when you needed it.

07:16.940 --> 07:18.980
Everything!

07:19.980 --> 07:22.240
That is everything.

07:22.240 --> 07:24.450
A roof over your head.
Food from our stove!

07:24.450 --> 07:25.450
Shut your mouth now.

07:26.380 --> 07:28.520
Back to bed!
Back!

07:29.520 --> 07:32.320
If either of you
leave this room,

07:32.320 --> 07:34.350
your boy is for the worms.

07:34.360 --> 07:35.360
Am I understood?

07:38.460 --> 07:40.430
Oh!

07:40.430 --> 07:41.430
Ch-Charlotte.

07:46.400 --> 07:47.580
Go.

08:50.670 --> 08:51.870
And you say he worked for you?

08:52.400 --> 08:56.010
Why do you keep asking the same questions?
This is madness.

08:56.010 --> 08:57.440
My husband would take in strays.

08:57.440 --> 08:59.650
He always said he was
willing to help anyone

08:59.650 --> 09:02.140
who would work an
honest day, so yes.

09:02.150 --> 09:04.680
He knew him.
They all knew him.

09:04.680 --> 09:06.550
Will you find my son?

09:06.550 --> 09:10.660
Well, it's a, uh... It's a lot
of land to cover, Mrs. Lockton.

09:10.660 --> 09:12.470
We'll do our best.

09:20.470 --> 09:23.570
If my husband knew him, then
you must have known him too.

09:23.570 --> 09:26.700
I've seen how you've befriended each and
every one of them that came through.

09:26.700 --> 09:28.540
Ma'am, I didn't.
I swear.

09:28.540 --> 09:29.770
They were your friends.

09:29.780 --> 09:33.310
I was only being welcoming like
Mr. Lockton would have wanted.

09:33.310 --> 09:35.680
- Tell me who it was.
- Ma'am...

09:36.680 --> 09:38.750
Look at me!

09:39.750 --> 09:41.590
Tell me who it was!

09:41.590 --> 09:43.320
I don't know who it was.

09:43.320 --> 09:46.060
- I didn't seem 'im up close.
- No.

09:46.060 --> 09:47.760
Then pack your bags! Now!

09:47.760 --> 09:49.410
Ma'am, please!

10:00.410 --> 10:03.680
Ma'am, it's been three months.

10:03.680 --> 10:05.750
And we're sorry,
Mrs. Lockton.

10:05.750 --> 10:08.350
We've looked high and low.

10:08.350 --> 10:10.520
We've combed
the entire district.

10:10.520 --> 10:12.290
My advice...

10:13.290 --> 10:14.560
is it's...

10:15.560 --> 10:17.260
It's time to move on.

10:54.260 --> 10:56.100
- Mrs. Lockton?
- Yes.

10:56.100 --> 10:57.740
From the post office.

11:05.710 --> 11:06.880
Ohh!

11:08.880 --> 11:10.150
Rider, wait!

11:10.150 --> 11:11.590
Wait! Ma'am?

11:14.590 --> 11:17.620
"Your son is alive and well.
Your son is alive."

11:18.620 --> 11:20.220
"If you want to see him again,

11:20.230 --> 11:23.290
place 500 pounds in the Bank
of New Zealand by Friday next

11:23.290 --> 11:25.630
to the account set up
in your husband's name.

11:25.630 --> 11:28.830
Attempt to trace the money
or go to the police

11:28.830 --> 11:30.730
and you will never see
your son again."

11:30.730 --> 11:33.730
W-When was this delivered to you?
Three days ago.

11:33.740 --> 11:34.870
From where?

11:34.870 --> 11:36.410
Pass me the envelope, ma'am.

11:37.410 --> 11:40.130
This was launched in Corktown. South
of here. About half a days away.

11:40.410 --> 11:41.410
How would I get there?

11:41.410 --> 11:43.180
There's a train
from Little Hills.

11:43.180 --> 11:45.590
But Corktown, Mrs. Lockton.
Will you be traveling alone?

11:46.590 --> 11:48.220
Yes.

11:48.220 --> 11:49.720
As soon as I can.

12:13.850 --> 12:15.250
Excuse me.

12:15.250 --> 12:17.460
Where's the post office? It's just there.

12:30.360 --> 12:31.830
Can I help you, miss?

12:31.830 --> 12:34.440
This was posted from here,
I believe.

12:36.440 --> 12:38.700
I believe
it would have been, yes.

12:38.700 --> 12:39.810
Did it originate here?

12:41.810 --> 12:43.340
Not so sure about that, miss.

12:43.340 --> 12:45.280
So it might have been shipped
from somewhere else?

12:45.280 --> 12:47.580
May well have done
exactly that, yes.

12:48.580 --> 12:49.580
Where?

12:49.580 --> 12:51.320
No idea.

12:51.320 --> 12:52.850
This town is
the end of the line.

12:52.850 --> 12:54.420
The other side of those hills,

12:54.420 --> 12:56.500
people are scattered every
which way for days on end.

12:58.460 --> 12:59.740
Sorry I couldn't be
of more help.

13:01.500 --> 13:03.700
Where might I find
the Bank of New Zealand?

13:05.700 --> 13:07.830
Well, you're looking at it.

13:07.840 --> 13:10.410
I'm the closest thing you'll
find this far from Nelson.

13:11.410 --> 13:13.440
You hold an account
in the name of Lockton.

13:13.440 --> 13:14.610
Lockton.

13:15.610 --> 13:16.690
Lockton.

13:25.690 --> 13:27.970
Looks like I can
finally help you today.

13:37.970 --> 13:39.500
Goldtown Hotel?

13:39.500 --> 13:41.370
All those accounts
are held there?

13:41.370 --> 13:43.310
Goldtown Hotel.
Aye.

13:43.310 --> 13:45.440
Diggers' money.

13:45.440 --> 13:48.380
It's held at hotel
before it gets sent to bank.

13:48.380 --> 13:49.940
Can I get there from here?

13:49.950 --> 13:52.850
If you're willing to travel
for a week.

13:52.850 --> 13:54.020
Maybe more.

13:54.020 --> 13:57.020
Only way through is
that mountain, see?

13:57.020 --> 14:00.320
Plenty of lunatics heading over
that way, chasing their fortune.

14:00.320 --> 14:02.030
Plenty heading back too.

14:02.030 --> 14:03.930
They're starving to death,
they are.

14:03.930 --> 14:06.060
But I can get over there,
from here?

14:06.060 --> 14:08.470
Ask the FrÃ¤ulein.

14:08.470 --> 14:11.370
She'll know when there's
a party heading out.

14:11.370 --> 14:12.880
Across the street there.

14:16.870 --> 14:18.880
No journey for a lady, miss.

14:20.880 --> 14:22.760
If you don't mind my saying so.

14:50.540 --> 14:52.040
Give the women the vote.

14:52.040 --> 14:53.780
Votes for women.

14:53.780 --> 14:55.650
Take a flyer.

14:55.650 --> 14:56.920
Votes for women.

15:01.920 --> 15:04.420
Looks like we just picked
the wrong time to leave.

15:04.420 --> 15:06.420
Don't mind me, missy.

15:06.420 --> 15:08.030
I'll see you later.

15:08.030 --> 15:10.960
I'll even pay you extra if you
keep that pretty little hat on.

15:13.000 --> 15:14.400
No, I'm not going down
any lower.

15:15.400 --> 15:17.370
No, no, don't be cheeky.

15:17.370 --> 15:19.740
Yeah.

15:19.740 --> 15:22.910
Oi! Copping a feel
without paying?

15:23.950 --> 15:26.010
Get off me.

15:26.010 --> 15:27.950
No.

15:28.950 --> 15:30.850
I'm looking for the FrÃ¤ulein.

15:30.850 --> 15:32.150
Are you working? No.

15:32.150 --> 15:34.020
Are you the FrÃ¤ulein?

15:34.020 --> 15:36.060
No. Right.

15:36.060 --> 15:37.990
Come on then.

15:38.990 --> 15:40.670
No! You'll
have to wait.

15:43.670 --> 15:44.670
Come along.

15:56.440 --> 15:58.850
Come here, darling.
I don't bite.

16:00.850 --> 16:01.850
Hey!

16:03.490 --> 16:04.770
Whoo!

16:22.740 --> 16:25.210
I was told there might be some
gentlemen heading to Goldtown.

16:25.210 --> 16:27.140
Gentlemen?

16:27.140 --> 16:30.020
There are none of those here.

16:33.020 --> 16:35.020
You're a digger?
No.

16:36.050 --> 16:38.820
Then only one other thing
you can be.

16:38.820 --> 16:42.890
And if you are,
you and me need a deal.

16:42.890 --> 16:47.130
No woman in Goldtown makes
money without dealing with me.

16:47.130 --> 16:50.600
I'm not a digger,
nor anything else.

16:50.600 --> 16:53.510
I just want to get to
Goldtown for my own reasons.

16:54.510 --> 16:55.910
Ten pounds. To get to Goldtown?

16:55.910 --> 16:57.980
Ten pounds!

17:00.980 --> 17:02.180
Bully!

17:04.180 --> 17:06.020
Tell Bully where you go.

17:10.020 --> 17:11.660
Excuse me?

17:14.660 --> 17:17.190
The FrÃ¤ulein says
you're heading to Goldtown.

17:17.200 --> 17:18.500
Aye.
In the morning.

17:18.500 --> 17:21.170
Taking supplies.

17:21.170 --> 17:22.670
Girls too.

17:23.670 --> 17:26.200
- Well, I'd like to come along.
- Would you?

17:26.200 --> 17:27.940
I've paid her to get there.

17:27.940 --> 17:30.210
No, you haven't.

17:30.210 --> 17:31.750
You paid FrÃ¤ulein...

17:33.750 --> 17:34.890
to get to me.

17:38.890 --> 17:41.260
So to get to Goldtown?

17:42.260 --> 17:43.990
Can you do that?

17:47.830 --> 17:50.230
Hmm? No.

17:50.230 --> 17:52.300
Or even that?

17:52.300 --> 17:54.870
Everything will be fine!
Everything will be fine!

17:58.870 --> 18:00.210
No.

18:03.210 --> 18:06.150
No. I can't.

18:06.150 --> 18:07.950
But...

18:08.950 --> 18:11.090
I can do this.

18:17.960 --> 18:19.170
Fifty.

18:32.170 --> 18:35.680
You know, you shouldn't be flashing
your jewelry around like that.

18:35.680 --> 18:37.310
Not in a place like this.

18:37.310 --> 18:40.810
And, uh,
you've just been fleeced.

18:40.820 --> 18:42.250
Not if you take me to Goldtown.

18:49.760 --> 18:52.170
Yee-haw!

19:01.170 --> 19:02.240
You still coming?

19:02.240 --> 19:03.870
That's what we discussed.

19:03.870 --> 19:06.750
See any whores on your way out?

19:12.750 --> 19:15.850
When you're ready,
get in that one.

19:15.850 --> 19:17.400
Thank you.

19:25.400 --> 19:26.700
Easier without this, miss.

19:35.710 --> 19:38.210
Thank you, ladies.
I'll have a look.

19:38.210 --> 19:39.640
Good luck!

19:39.650 --> 19:41.010
One day, we're gonna vote.

19:41.010 --> 19:44.020
Women are gonna vote and two fingers
to anyone who tries to stop us.

19:44.020 --> 19:45.970
You'll still be a two-bit whore.
Aye.

19:45.970 --> 19:47.960
A two-bit whore with a vote,
though, eh?

19:55.960 --> 19:59.830
Jesus.
Two weeks in that shitbox?

19:59.830 --> 20:03.050
You really know how to make
a girl feel special.

20:19.050 --> 20:21.020
Silk.

20:23.020 --> 20:24.020
Silk.

21:07.070 --> 21:08.070
So you're a dancer?

21:08.900 --> 21:11.070
She look like a bloody dancer?

21:11.070 --> 21:13.510
Never turned a trick
neither, I bet.

21:13.510 --> 21:14.980
What's your name?

21:15.980 --> 21:16.910
Charlotte.

21:16.910 --> 21:19.010
That's a pretty name.

21:19.010 --> 21:19.950
I'm Heather.

21:19.950 --> 21:23.450
That's Flamenco.
Well, we call her Flamenco.

21:23.450 --> 21:24.950
What's your real name again?

21:24.950 --> 21:27.350
Maria Theresa
Angelica Evita Pasimos.

21:27.350 --> 21:29.320
Flamenco.

21:30.320 --> 21:31.860
What are you doing here?

21:31.860 --> 21:34.109
There's plenty of people
who need Goldtown's

21:34.121 --> 21:35.830
money more than
the likes of you.

21:35.830 --> 21:38.040
What would you know
about the likes of me?

21:40.040 --> 21:43.250
You're a snotty bitch,
that much I do know.

21:48.250 --> 21:49.480
That's Honey.

23:09.600 --> 23:11.870
What do you think you're doing?
Those are mine.

23:13.870 --> 23:17.240
I asked you what do you think you're doing?
Those are my shoes.

23:17.240 --> 23:18.970
Looks to me like
you've got plenty.

23:18.970 --> 23:21.140
You have no right to steal.

23:21.140 --> 23:24.180
So take them back.
Go ahead.

23:25.180 --> 23:26.910
<i>Vamos.</i>

23:26.910 --> 23:28.260
Take them off me.

23:41.260 --> 23:43.270
There.

23:44.270 --> 23:46.100
It's a matching set.

23:46.100 --> 23:48.140
If you're feeling generous,
I'll take the petticoat.

24:00.450 --> 24:02.450
That...

24:02.450 --> 24:04.320
Give me back... Where's my...

24:07.220 --> 24:09.460
You stole my money!

24:13.000 --> 24:14.500
Ladies.
Ladies.

24:16.500 --> 24:18.330
First night.

24:19.330 --> 24:21.290
She stole my money.
I take her shoes.

24:21.290 --> 24:23.500
- My shoes and my money.
- Is it in there?

24:23.510 --> 24:27.310
No, but she's wearing my shoes,
so she must have taken my money.

24:29.310 --> 24:31.510
Someone else
must have taken it then.

24:31.510 --> 24:34.280
Aye, so, uh,

24:34.280 --> 24:36.350
now you're accusing
the rest of us, eh?

24:36.350 --> 24:39.390
No, but all the money
I had in that bag is gone.

24:39.390 --> 24:42.090
Oh, would that be the stash that you
were flashing around last night?

24:42.090 --> 24:44.130
Like it was everyone else's
but your own?

24:44.130 --> 24:47.060
You stayed the night
at Madame FrÃ¤ulein's.

24:47.060 --> 24:50.370
The moment you closed your eyes,

24:50.370 --> 24:53.370
you waved good-bye
to everything you own.

24:56.370 --> 24:59.680
Just be thankful we're going
to Goldtown, princess.

24:59.680 --> 25:03.420
You wouldn't believe what some will
pay to see you flash your titties.

26:28.840 --> 26:30.370
We should bury him.

26:30.370 --> 26:34.150
Waste of time. Birds gotta
eat, same as worms.

26:38.140 --> 26:39.450
We're moving on.

27:11.410 --> 27:12.680
Shoot it.

27:14.680 --> 27:16.890
Go, go, go, go, go!

27:31.470 --> 27:33.870
Let's make this easy,
eh, fellas?

27:33.870 --> 27:36.340
All we want is the food.

27:36.340 --> 27:39.240
And the whiskey.

27:39.240 --> 27:43.280
Maybe these lasses for the ride.
And we'll be on our way.

27:45.280 --> 27:46.725
It's not gonna happen, pal.

27:46.737 --> 27:49.450
Then you've just come to
the end of the line, pal!

29:07.870 --> 29:09.000
It's all right.

29:13.940 --> 29:16.780
You might want to look away.

29:54.320 --> 29:56.950
You've got the wrong leg!

29:56.950 --> 29:58.950
Oh! Ah!

30:05.430 --> 30:07.060
And then what at the end?

30:07.060 --> 30:09.000
It's finished!

30:12.800 --> 30:13.800
We'll practice, okay?

30:16.710 --> 30:18.040
Come on, princess.

30:18.040 --> 30:21.010
Let your hair down
for once in your life.

30:21.010 --> 30:22.950
You're alive.

30:29.320 --> 30:30.990
You mind?

30:30.990 --> 30:32.530
I would like that.

30:42.500 --> 30:44.640
There must be
something special...

30:45.640 --> 30:46.610
in Goldtown.

30:46.610 --> 30:48.640
For a lady like you
to do something like this.

30:50.640 --> 30:54.650
My son. He was stolen by
the man who killed my husband.

30:57.650 --> 30:59.720
And you think he's in Goldtown?

31:01.720 --> 31:03.720
You know who he is? The man? No.

31:03.920 --> 31:08.890
If you start knocking on doors,
you see, word will spread fast.

31:08.890 --> 31:11.130
So you need to move faster.

31:12.130 --> 31:14.400
Do you live there in Goldtown?

31:14.400 --> 31:16.800
We work for the boss,
but we're not diggers.

31:18.670 --> 31:20.170
So, say you find this boy.

31:20.170 --> 31:22.010
I will find my son.

31:23.010 --> 31:25.010
Then what?

31:25.010 --> 31:27.380
I was gonna pay him.
The man.

31:27.380 --> 31:31.650
You think it would be that simple
after he killed your husband?

31:31.650 --> 31:34.920
Well, it'll be 10 times
less simple without money.

31:37.920 --> 31:38.920
I don't know.

31:44.900 --> 31:46.630
I will steal him back.

31:46.640 --> 31:48.540
You got a gun?

31:48.540 --> 31:51.100
Do you even know
how to shoot it?

31:52.100 --> 31:55.110
Ah.
In the name of the wee man.

31:57.440 --> 31:59.480
Well, we're still a week away.

31:59.480 --> 32:01.850
We'll have to do
something about that.

32:01.850 --> 32:03.720
Thank you.

32:03.720 --> 32:05.650
Don't thank me.

32:05.650 --> 32:07.090
Not till the boy's
back in your arms.

32:07.460 --> 32:09.520
And for what it's worth,

32:09.530 --> 32:11.730
what you just told me there...

32:12.730 --> 32:14.490
you shouldn't have told me
any of that.

32:14.490 --> 32:16.960
Not a single word.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.460
In case you don't know who I am.

32:18.470 --> 32:19.770
Yes, I do.
You saved my life.

32:19.770 --> 32:22.740
Even someone who saves
your life, princess.

32:22.740 --> 32:24.910
You don't tell them stuff
like that, okay?

32:29.850 --> 32:31.910
I'd make some friends.

32:31.920 --> 32:34.630
Christ, eh? You're gonna
need them where we're going.

32:43.630 --> 32:46.160
We're a man down. We gotta
know you can defend yourselves.

32:46.160 --> 32:48.530
Again.

32:48.530 --> 32:51.630
You can act fast. He's not gonna
stand there waiting for you to aim,

32:51.640 --> 32:53.100
so shoot your bloody guns.

32:53.100 --> 32:55.710
Ah!

32:55.710 --> 32:57.810
Well, at least
one of you will live.

32:57.810 --> 32:59.740
Again.

32:59.740 --> 33:02.510
You're thinking too much.
Come on. Again.

33:03.510 --> 33:05.080
I'm gonna count to ten.

33:05.080 --> 33:08.480
One, two, three...

33:08.490 --> 33:10.920
When you gotta shoot, shoot.
Don't think.

33:12.920 --> 33:14.840
Reload. Again.

34:06.880 --> 34:08.880
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

34:09.880 --> 34:10.980
Come on.

34:10.980 --> 34:12.920
Come on!

34:12.920 --> 34:14.550
Come on! Come on.

34:14.550 --> 34:16.260
Step off!

34:19.260 --> 34:21.190
Hunter.

34:21.190 --> 34:23.560
Come on.
Let's get a move on.

34:23.560 --> 34:26.100
It's not the river.
It's the wagon.

34:26.100 --> 34:29.040
Matai, Klaus, unhitch the wagon.

34:29.040 --> 34:30.800
Right.
Everyone out.

34:30.810 --> 34:32.810
Why?
Because we're stopping here.

34:34.780 --> 34:37.010
Move your asses.
Come on.

34:39.010 --> 34:43.949
Don't tell me there ain't an easier
way to get to Goldtown than this.

34:44.949 --> 34:47.290
It's the axle, boss.

34:47.290 --> 34:49.159
We'll figure it out.

34:49.159 --> 34:50.790
It's busted.

34:50.790 --> 34:52.699
Hunter, we'll figure it out.

34:57.700 --> 34:58.910
What's that on her neck?

35:02.900 --> 35:04.640
It's a tattoo.

35:04.640 --> 35:06.770
A tattoo of what?

35:06.770 --> 35:08.180
Prison.

35:09.180 --> 35:10.980
She spent six years as a maid.

35:10.980 --> 35:12.980
But being told what to do
her whole life

35:12.980 --> 35:15.220
sent her spitting
in the master's food.

35:15.220 --> 35:17.390
And a lot else besides.

35:17.390 --> 35:20.090
Locked up for three years.

35:20.090 --> 35:22.360
Was Flamenco in prison too? Nah.

35:22.360 --> 35:23.990
Shipwreck or some such.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.330
She survived,
but her family didn't.

35:26.330 --> 35:28.060
Pretty girl like that though.

35:28.060 --> 35:32.370
She can make her way. If she
can stomach what it takes.

35:32.370 --> 35:33.680
And you?

35:42.680 --> 35:43.750
All right, pull!

35:47.750 --> 35:49.750
Got it?
Yeah.

35:49.990 --> 35:52.320
Just get it in there.

35:52.320 --> 35:53.960
Hold on, one second.

35:53.960 --> 35:55.330
Yeah!

35:56.330 --> 35:57.660
Come on! Faster!

35:59.660 --> 36:02.870
Put your back in it, man!

36:02.870 --> 36:03.970
That's it!

36:05.970 --> 36:07.000
Bully!

36:07.010 --> 36:08.910
Hey! Hey!

36:08.910 --> 36:11.080
The axle.
It's pinning him down.

36:11.080 --> 36:14.240
He was stuck on the axle.
Lift it! Lift that pole!

36:14.240 --> 36:15.780
Lift it up!
Get it off him!

36:15.780 --> 36:17.380
Come on!
Get him off the axle!

36:17.380 --> 36:18.450
One, two, three!
Go! Pull!

36:19.450 --> 36:21.390
Please, God.

36:22.390 --> 36:24.120
No! Get him up!

36:24.120 --> 36:25.720
Come on!

36:25.720 --> 36:27.360
Come on!
Get this stuff off!

36:27.360 --> 36:29.190
Hurry up, hurry up!

36:29.190 --> 36:31.000
Help him, please!
Somebody!

36:31.000 --> 36:33.170
Lift! Lift him!

36:33.170 --> 36:35.870
Ain't you ever lifted, boy?

36:35.870 --> 36:38.740
Come on!
Get it off! Come on!

36:38.740 --> 36:40.740
Clear that stuff!
Come on! Come on!

36:41.740 --> 36:42.740
Come on, man!

36:43.440 --> 36:44.440
Two, three, go!

36:45.440 --> 36:47.280
Come on!

36:47.280 --> 36:48.750
Come on, man!

37:24.050 --> 37:27.520
We get the wagon loaded with whatever
we can manage, and we move on.

37:27.520 --> 37:29.250
We're never gonna make it.

37:29.260 --> 37:31.890
So what are you suggesting
we do instead, sweetheart?

37:31.890 --> 37:34.030
Turn back.
Get home alive, at least.

37:34.030 --> 37:35.800
You saying I can't get us there?

37:35.800 --> 37:38.370
Are you saying you can?

37:39.370 --> 37:40.900
Fine.

37:40.900 --> 37:42.940
Turn back.

37:42.940 --> 37:45.210
I'll bury you on the way back.

37:45.210 --> 37:47.040
I need to get to Goldtown.

37:47.040 --> 37:48.980
There's no point
in arriving dead.

37:48.980 --> 37:51.210
I'll show you dead, bitch!

37:51.210 --> 37:53.780
You want to see dead?
I'll give you dead!

37:53.780 --> 37:56.480
Hunter! Hunter!

37:56.480 --> 38:00.160
Leave her be.

38:05.460 --> 38:06.900
All right.

38:06.900 --> 38:09.000
We make the wagon good.

38:09.000 --> 38:12.420
We move on, and we camp by dark.

39:32.990 --> 39:34.990
See, here's the thing.

39:35.990 --> 39:37.490
You don't look like a whore.

39:44.130 --> 39:45.130
Mmm.

39:46.600 --> 39:49.270
You don't smell like a whore.

39:50.270 --> 39:52.610
I wonder what you do
do like a whore.

39:57.610 --> 39:59.050
<i>Hola, guapo.</i>

40:00.050 --> 40:02.220
