44:47.280 --> 44:49.510
I'll be doing the negotiating
on your behalf.

44:49.510 --> 44:52.590
Make sure you're well kept,
safe and well fed.

44:52.590 --> 44:55.220
And all for a mere
35 percent of your takings.

44:55.220 --> 44:56.890
Wait.
Are you the boss?

44:56.890 --> 44:59.260
No.
Mr. McCullen is the boss.

44:59.260 --> 45:01.530
Aye. Then it's Mr.
McCullen we work for.

45:01.530 --> 45:02.890
As do I.

45:02.890 --> 45:04.700
It's his 35 percent, not mine.

45:04.700 --> 45:07.800
Twenty percent or I glue
my bloomers to my ass.

45:07.800 --> 45:12.540
Well, perhaps we could come to some
kind of quid pro quo arrangement.

45:12.540 --> 45:15.710
Just show us the rooms,
you dirty little bastard.

45:15.710 --> 45:18.280
It's good to have a friend
sometimes, you know.

45:18.280 --> 45:19.950
Aye, it depends on the friend. Right.

45:19.950 --> 45:20.950
Onwards and upwards.

45:21.480 --> 45:23.320
This is just like the big house.

45:23.320 --> 45:24.790
How many bloody stairs?

45:27.290 --> 45:30.960
Here's where you'll be
providing your fleshy pleasures.

45:30.960 --> 45:33.290
And over here,

45:33.290 --> 45:37.300
yet another little love grotto from
which to sing your siren songs.

45:39.300 --> 45:40.740
And over here,

45:40.740 --> 45:43.440
we have the grand suite.

45:43.440 --> 45:45.770
And the last but not the least,

45:45.770 --> 45:47.580
the not so grand suite.

45:48.580 --> 45:49.710
Very funny.

45:51.980 --> 45:55.550
Hey, what happened to the dresses?
We were promised good dresses.

45:55.550 --> 45:58.750
If Mr. McCullen gave his word,
he'll keep his word.

45:58.750 --> 46:02.830
Right. I'm gonna leave you lovely ladies
to make yourselves even lovelier.

46:03.830 --> 46:05.660
You won't be shy
of work tonight.

46:05.660 --> 46:07.060
That's for certain.

46:08.060 --> 46:09.570
Oh, shit.

46:09.570 --> 46:11.830
Won't be making anything
looking like this.

46:34.830 --> 46:36.900
They never leave you, do they?

46:41.900 --> 46:44.040
She was three.

47:01.350 --> 47:03.390
Gentlemen!
Both the drink and the ladies

47:03.390 --> 47:05.690
await your unbridled
appreciation.

47:10.990 --> 47:14.670
Well, it appears there are some
things more desirable than gold.

47:15.670 --> 47:16.840
Hello.

47:18.840 --> 47:21.080
So pleased to meet you all.

47:23.080 --> 47:24.440
Ooh, buy us some drinks.

47:24.440 --> 47:25.950
Buy me a drink?

47:27.950 --> 47:29.510
Another one.

47:30.510 --> 47:31.820
I'm so excited!

47:35.090 --> 47:37.160
Thank you.
Oh, thank you.

47:39.160 --> 47:40.960
So who's going to help me?

47:41.960 --> 47:43.100
Oh, sorry.

47:43.100 --> 47:44.100
Sorry.

47:55.010 --> 47:56.610
S-Sorry.

47:59.510 --> 48:01.180
Hello. Are you for sale?

48:01.180 --> 48:02.580
- No.
- But why?

48:02.580 --> 48:04.580
Stop it!
Give you good money.

48:04.580 --> 48:06.690
Stay with me.

48:15.460 --> 48:18.130
- Are you leaving?
- Job is done, miss.

48:19.130 --> 48:21.200
I wanted to say thank you.

48:21.200 --> 48:23.140
You be safe, now.

48:24.140 --> 48:26.140
Are you leaving too?

48:27.140 --> 48:28.610
This is not my home.

48:29.610 --> 48:30.880
I never asked your name.

48:30.880 --> 48:31.880
Matai.

48:32.480 --> 48:34.620
How often do you come
to Goldtown, Matai?

48:34.620 --> 48:36.920
When somebody needs
to get over the mountain.

48:36.920 --> 48:37.920
And say somebody did.

48:38.480 --> 48:40.020
Already you don't like it?

48:40.020 --> 48:41.720
It's not my home either.

48:41.720 --> 48:43.560
I was never planning on staying.

48:43.560 --> 48:44.560
I'll need help leaving.

48:45.490 --> 48:47.600
I can return.

48:49.600 --> 48:51.630
I don't know how long I'll need.

48:51.630 --> 48:53.470
Are you in trouble,
Miss Charlotte?

48:57.470 --> 48:59.150
I can be back in three days.

49:02.140 --> 49:04.040
Three days. Yes.
Thank you, three days.

49:33.040 --> 49:35.200
Hello.

50:03.210 --> 50:04.640
Oh.

50:04.640 --> 50:07.250
- Give reason I no pull trigger.

50:08.410 --> 50:11.050
I'm sorry. I heard crying,
and I thought the baby was sick.

50:11.050 --> 50:12.950
No sick. No. I'm sorry.

50:12.950 --> 50:15.720
- Are there any other families
here?

50:15.720 --> 50:17.990
You go now.
You no come again.

50:17.990 --> 50:19.860
Who took that portrait?
Who took that picture?

50:19.860 --> 50:21.730
- I say go!
- I have the same picture.

50:21.730 --> 50:24.060
I'm going!
I'm going!

50:25.060 --> 50:26.910
Gone.

51:18.890 --> 51:23.320
Oh, there you are.

51:23.330 --> 51:25.760
I thought you might be upstairs,
earning yourself some money.

51:25.760 --> 51:27.960
A lot of the fellas want a
taste of your wares, darlin'.

51:28.800 --> 51:30.400
Listen, walk with me.

51:30.400 --> 51:31.400
Gentlemen.

51:36.910 --> 51:39.910
If you want a bed,
a nice roof over your head,

51:39.910 --> 51:42.080
lovely fires to keep you warm,

51:42.080 --> 51:44.880
then you do what the other girlies
are doing that you rode in with.

51:44.880 --> 51:48.220
Either up there on the stage
or flat on your back.

51:48.220 --> 51:49.690
Because it's either that,

51:49.690 --> 51:52.220
or you're out the door,
and you don't come back.

51:52.220 --> 51:54.220
That's how it works.

51:54.220 --> 51:55.760
Show's in an hour.

52:01.770 --> 52:04.400
Oh, did you see their faces?

52:04.400 --> 52:06.370
They look loaded.

52:09.370 --> 52:11.210
Very nice.

52:16.210 --> 52:18.010
Is there a dress I can wear?

52:33.100 --> 52:38.010
Whoo!

52:46.010 --> 52:48.010
Whoo!

52:57.020 --> 52:58.330
Go on, girls.

53:01.330 --> 53:02.800
Oh, keep it comin'.

53:04.800 --> 53:05.800
Yes!
Oh, yeah.

53:21.750 --> 53:25.290
Oh, yeah.

53:34.390 --> 53:36.800
- Marry me!
- Which one of us?

53:36.800 --> 53:38.470
Any of you! All of you!

53:42.340 --> 53:45.070
Oh, Mr. McCullen. We weren't
expecting you back tonight.

53:45.070 --> 53:48.010
How was your day? Good, Bertie.
Thank you.

53:48.010 --> 53:52.110
So, uh, all this is yours,
the hotel? You got a wife?

53:52.110 --> 53:55.050
Mr. McCullen prefers his toffees
with the wrappers untouched.

53:57.050 --> 54:00.260
But a horse is a damn sight easier
to ride if it's been broken in.

54:04.260 --> 54:06.230
Hey.
Boss.

54:06.230 --> 54:07.830
What about Bully?

54:07.830 --> 54:09.230
He didn't make it.

54:09.230 --> 54:10.830
The gorge.

54:10.830 --> 54:12.170
We lost some supplies too.

54:12.170 --> 54:14.800
We lost too many lives
in that pass.

54:14.800 --> 54:16.270
We'll say prayers
for him Sunday.

54:21.940 --> 54:24.550
I'll send the Jameson brothers
for the supplies in the morning.

54:26.550 --> 54:28.220
Bertie?

54:28.220 --> 54:29.860
I think these ladies need a drink. Right.

54:45.600 --> 54:47.540
So.

54:47.540 --> 54:49.270
What do you cost me? No!

54:49.270 --> 54:52.010
- You don't like my money?
- That's not what I said.

54:52.010 --> 54:54.180
- You don't like me?
- Actually, I do quite like you.

54:54.180 --> 54:56.880
- My money's good, Bertie!
- I know that, Freckles.

54:56.880 --> 54:58.150
But you heard the lady.

54:58.150 --> 55:00.420
What the hell
kind of a place is this?

55:00.420 --> 55:03.160
I've got good money to spend
here for Christ's sakes!

55:08.160 --> 55:10.590
That's the last help
you'll get from me.

55:10.600 --> 55:12.310
From now on, you'll fight
them off yourself.

55:13.160 --> 55:14.900
Here. On the house.

55:14.900 --> 55:16.470
Help you to relax.

55:16.470 --> 55:17.680
Maybe loosen you up a little.

55:57.680 --> 55:58.680
I don't think so.

56:01.510 --> 56:03.150
Dangerous out there, princess.

56:06.150 --> 56:08.296
Mr. McCullen doesn't
like his ladies getting

56:08.308 --> 56:10.130
into trouble, losing
their looks now.

56:11.130 --> 56:12.430
Oh.

56:13.430 --> 56:16.430
Wouldn't mind us getting a bit
of fresh air, now, would he?

56:18.430 --> 56:20.910
Got a window in my room. All the
fresh air you need, Charlotte.

56:23.500 --> 56:24.500
Charlotte.

56:25.670 --> 56:27.270
That's the kind of name
you just wanna...

56:28.610 --> 56:30.270
wrap your mouth around,
now, isn't it?

56:56.270 --> 56:59.210
First honest days' work you've ever
done in your life, eh, princess?

57:00.210 --> 57:02.280
So what's he up to,
this McCullen?

57:02.280 --> 57:04.550
That's "Mr. McCullen"
to you.

57:04.550 --> 57:08.420
And what he's up to is making a life for
himself after all he's been through.

57:08.420 --> 57:11.620
Losing his wife and his
child, and all that he had.

57:11.620 --> 57:14.260
Some folk would simply
fall to pieces.

57:14.260 --> 57:16.560
Others stand up.
They look to their future.

57:16.560 --> 57:18.190
That's what your man's done.

57:18.190 --> 57:19.640
He's got some big plans
for Goldtown.

57:20.500 --> 57:22.200
Some grand old plans.

57:22.200 --> 57:24.710
Right.
It's time for work.

57:30.710 --> 57:32.210
Michael?

57:32.210 --> 57:34.340
Get those fucking chairs down.

57:40.080 --> 57:42.790
Right, gentlemen.
The house is open.

57:42.790 --> 57:45.190
One pound for the English
rose over there,

57:45.190 --> 57:47.160
just sitting there doing
nothing the whole time.

57:47.160 --> 57:48.290
One pound for a dance.

57:48.290 --> 57:51.330
Yes, well, fair's fair.
After all, business is business.

57:51.330 --> 57:54.060
Two pounds. Two pounds.
Any advance on two pounds?

57:54.060 --> 57:55.300
Come on, Bertie.
Three pounds.

57:55.300 --> 57:56.300
Three pounds!

57:56.500 --> 57:57.670
Four pounds, Bertie.

57:57.670 --> 57:59.670
I believe we have a winner.

58:00.200 --> 58:02.410
Oh, come on then, love.

